<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Sat, 11 Apr 2026 12:33:23 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>运动诱导线粒体超复合物的性别特异性组装</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/exercise-induces-sex-specific-assembly-of-mitochondrial-supercomplexes</link><description>运动中线粒体超级复合体的组装。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/exercise-induces-sex-specific-assembly-of-mitochondrial-supercomplexes2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 11 Apr 2026 12:33:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/exercise-induces-sex-specific-assembly-of-mitochondrial-supercomplexes</guid></item><item><title>1990年至2023年全球儿童和青少年癌症负担（0-19岁）：2023年全球疾病负担研究的系统分析</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/the-global-burden-of-childhood-and-adolescent-cancer-age-0-19-years-from-1990-to-2023-a-systematic-analysis-for-the-global-burden-of-disease-study-2023</link><description>据估计，到 2023 年，急性淋巴细胞白血病以及脑部和中枢神经系统癌症将成为 0-19 岁儿童新发癌症病例的最大诱因。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/the-global-burden-of-childhood-and-adolescent-cancer-age-0-19-years-from-1990-to-2023-a-systematic-analysis-for-the-global-burden-of-disease-study-2023.gif" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 11 Apr 2026 12:18:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/the-global-burden-of-childhood-and-adolescent-cancer-age-0-19-years-from-1990-to-2023-a-systematic-analysis-for-the-global-burden-of-disease-study-2023</guid></item><item><title>心血管成像中的人工智能：风险、缓解措施和安全实施之路</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/artificial-intelligence-in-cardiovascular-imaging-risks-mitigations-and-the-path-to-safe-implementation</link><description>人工智能 (AI) 通过自动执行图像分割、特征提取和风险预测等任务，正在迅速改变心血管成像，从而显着提高诊断精度和效率。然而，将人工智能融入临床工作流程会带来重大风险，必须解决这些风险，以确保安全可靠的患者护理。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/artificial-intelligence-in-cardiovascular-imaging-risks-mitigations-and-the-path-to-safe-implementation2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 11 Apr 2026 12:03:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/artificial-intelligence-in-cardiovascular-imaging-risks-mitigations-and-the-path-to-safe-implementation</guid></item><item><title>人类为什么不能再生四肢？新研究提供了线索</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/why-cant-humans-regenerate-limbs-new-research-offers-a-clue</link><description>假设您不小心切掉了指尖。尤其是如果这种情况发生在你小时候，那么它很有可能会重新长出来——皮肤、指甲等等。对于猴子和老鼠等其他哺乳动物来说也是如此。然而不幸的是，我们的再生能力仅限于此。虽然其他一些生物，尤其是蝾螈和海星，可以再生整个四肢，但哺乳动物不具备这种进化超能力。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/why-cant-humans-regenerate-limbs-new-research-offers-a-clue.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 11 Apr 2026 11:48:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/why-cant-humans-regenerate-limbs-new-research-offers-a-clue</guid></item><item><title>宏观磁铁进动</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/a-macroscopic-magnet-precesses</link><description>孤立磁体的固有角动量会引起陀螺运动，这种观察可能会导致超灵敏磁力计的诞生。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/a-macroscopic-magnet-precesses.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 11 Apr 2026 11:33:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/a-macroscopic-magnet-precesses</guid></item><item><title>40 年后在二维领域得到证实的通用表面生长定律</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/universal-surface-growth-law-confirmed-in-two-dimensions-after-40-years</link><description>晶体、细菌菌落、火焰锋：表面的生长在 20 世纪 80 年代首次由 Kardar-Parisi-Zhang 方程描述。从那时起，它就被视为物理学的基本模型，对数学、生物学和计算机科学都有影响。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/universal-surface-growth-law-confirmed-in-two-dimensions-after-40-years.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 11 Apr 2026 11:18:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/universal-surface-growth-law-confirmed-in-two-dimensions-after-40-years</guid></item><item><title>双频保罗陷阱显示出在 CERN 之外合成反氢的潜力</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/dual-frequency-paul-trap-shows-potential-for-synthesizing-antihydrogen-outside-of-cern</link><description>一种新型射频陷阱可以捕获具有极其不同要求的粒子，并且理论上可以同时捕获两种类型的粒子。来自 PRISMA++ 卓越集群和美因茨约翰内斯古腾堡大学 (JGU) 亥姆霍兹研究所的 Dmitry Budker 教授小组的研究人员能够在同一装置中捕获钙离子或电子。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/dual-frequency-paul-trap-shows-potential-for-synthesizing-antihydrogen-outside-of-cern2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 11 Apr 2026 11:03:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/dual-frequency-paul-trap-shows-potential-for-synthesizing-antihydrogen-outside-of-cern</guid></item><item><title>嫦娥任务样本揭示月球外源有机物如何演化</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/change-mission-samples-reveal-how-exogenous-organic-matter-evolves-on-the-moon</link><description>生命必需的元素，如碳、氮、氧、磷和硫，是在太阳系的早期阶段通过小行星和彗星撞击地球和月球表面而“输送”到地球和月球的。这些外源物质可能提供了地球生命起源和早期进化所需的化学构件。但地球上广泛的地质活动和生物过程在很大程度上抹去了这些早期输入对我们星球的直接记录。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/change-mission-samples-reveal-how-exogenous-organic-matter-evolves-on-the-moon2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 11 Apr 2026 10:48:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/change-mission-samples-reveal-how-exogenous-organic-matter-evolves-on-the-moon</guid></item><item><title>水下建筑师：慈鲷的筑巢揭示的不仅仅是与生俱来的本能</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/underwater-architects-nest-building-in-cichlids-reveals-more-than-hardwired-instinct</link><description>我们将巢与庇护所、温暖和安全的避难所联系在一起，通常会想象用树枝、草和羽毛建造的鸟巢。然而，许多其他动物也利用了这样的庇护所，从白蚁到类人猿等多种物种建造巢穴，其多种多样的形式和用于建造巢穴的材料种类繁多，令人印象深刻。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/underwater-architects-nest-building-in-cichlids-reveals-more-than-hardwired-instinct.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 11 Apr 2026 10:33:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/underwater-architects-nest-building-in-cichlids-reveals-more-than-hardwired-instinct</guid></item><item><title>科学家发现f区金属产生新的氧结合化学</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/scientists-discover-f-block-metals-yield-new-oxygen-binding-chemistry</link><description>铁和氧在整个身体中结合在一起。最著名的是，铁与血红蛋白中的双氧或彼此配对的两个氧结合，通过血液输送氧气。但铁氧化合物（正如它们所称的那样）存在于全身的许多其他地方。例如，高活性的氧化铁用于代谢药物的肝酶。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/scientists-discover-f-block-metals-yield-new-oxygen-binding-chemistry.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 11 Apr 2026 10:18:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/scientists-discover-f-block-metals-yield-new-oxygen-binding-chemistry</guid></item></channel></rss>